'''Ime Daniel Okon''' (born 20 February 2004) is a South African professional [[soccer]] player who plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]] for [[Hannover 96]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

==Early life==
Okon was born in 2004 in South Africa. He attended Florida Park High School in South Africa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://capetown.today/the-emergence-of-ime-okon-a-rising-star-in-south-african-football/|title=The Emergence of Ime Okon: A Rising Star in South African Football|date=16 March 2024 |publisher=capetown.today}}</ref>

==Club career==
Okon started his career with South African side [[SuperSport United F.C.|SuperSport United]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://soccernews24.co.za/2023/09/22/ime-okon-key-to-supersport-united-defensive-prowess/|title=Ime Okon key to Supersport United's defensive prowess|publisher=soccernews24.co.za}}</ref> He joined German club [[Hannover 96]] ahead of the [[2025–26 Hannover 96 season|2025–26 season]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/hannover-holt-spannenden-okon-aus-suedafrika-1128978/artikel |title=Hannover holt "spannenden" Okon aus Südafrika |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |date=1 July 2025 |access-date=1 July 2025 |language=de}}</ref>

==International career==
Okon made his debut for the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]] on 4 June 2025 in the opening match of the [[2025 COSAFA Cup]] against [[Mozambique national football team|Mozambique]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2025-06-04/south-africa-vs-mozambique/3719201/ |title=Match Report of South Africa vs Mozambique |website=globalsportsarchive.com |publisher=Global Sports Archive |date=4 June 2025 |access-date=23 August 2025}}</ref> He scored his first goal three days later in the second tournament match against [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2025-06-07/south-africa-vs-zimbabwe/3719207/ |title=Match Report of South Africa vs Zimbabwe |website=globalsportsarchive.com |publisher=Global Sports Archive |date=7 June 2025 |access-date=23 August 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Okon is a native of [[Florida, Gauteng|Florida]], South Africa. He was born to a Nigerian father and South African mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.snl24.com/kickoff/sanews/bafana/ime-okon-from-high-school-to-bafana-call-up-20230823|title=Ime Okon - from high school to Bafana call-up|date=23 August 2023 |publisher=snl24.com}}</ref> He is the brother of South African [[Sprint (running)|sprinter]] [[Udeme Okon]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Luthuli |first=Lusanda |date=2 September 2024 |title=Ime Okon Hails Brother Udeme's Stunning Gold At World Champs |url=https://www.snl24.com/soccerladuma/fan-park/ime-okon-expresses-pride-in-athlete-brother-udeme-for-u20-world-championships-gold-medal-20240902 |access-date=18 November 2024 |website=SNL}}</ref>

